<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-36-1013 </DOCNO><TEXT>The Japanese market for heat pumps is the largest in the world as regardsquantity and, unlike the European one, is undergoing continuous development,mainy due to the strong needs for air conditioning and dehumidificationthat are characteristic of the country's climate. This is most particularlysymbolized by the reversible individual aparatus called the ''Room Airconditioner'' used for the air conditioning and heating of a room. Afterhaving established the importance of the market, the present articleoffers the recent technological innovations likely to modify in the shortrun the French heat pump market.</TEXT></DOC>